com.defano.jmonet.canvas.layer

Class ImageLayerSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.defano.jmonet.canvas.layer.ImageLayerSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LayeredImage

    public class ImageLayerSet
extends Object
implements LayeredImage
    A set of images rendered by layering one atop another. Each layer specifies an AlphaComposite mode to use during rendering.

        public void addLayer(ImageLayer layer)

        When producing an image from a ChangeSet, each layer image is drawn atop the previous using the AlphaComposite associated with it.

        layer - The image layer to add to the set.

      • isRemovingPaint

        public boolean isRemovingPaint()
        Determines if any layer in this image "removes" paint from the image it is drawn atop (as a result of using the AlphaComposite.DST_OUT composite mode. For example, a LayerSet produced by the eraser tool would "remove" paint.
        Returns:
        True if this set of changes removes paint from the source it is drawn atop; false otherwise.

      • isAddingPaint

        public boolean isAddingPaint()
        Determines if any layer in this images "adds" paint from the image it is drawn atop. For example, a LayerSet produced by the brush tool would "add" paint.
        Returns:
        True if this set of changes adds paint to the source it is drawn atop; false otherwise.
